The National Working Committee (NWC) of the ruling All Progressives Congress (APC) has finally cleared an aspirant, Babatunde Irukera, to contest the party’s Kogi governorship primaries. His clearance came few hours after a protest staged by his supporters at the APC National Secretariat in Abuja. The APC National Publicity Secretary, Malam Lanre Issa-Onilu, said in a statement yesterday that Irukera ‘successfully’ met the conditions provided by the party’s guidelines for the nomination of candidates within the time granted to clarify his claims. OVER 5,000 NIGERIAN MEN HAVE  OVERCOME POOR BEDROOM PERFORMANCE SYNDROME DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY The APC governorship primary holds today in the Confluence State. Supporters of disqualified Kogi gov’ship aspirant storm APC hqts Kogi governorship: 9 aspirants to run for APC primaries …Supporters of disqualified aspirant storm APC headquarters Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin